_source: {'play_name': 'Troilus and Cressida', 'speech_number': 33, 'line_number': '4.4.100', 'text_entry': 'And sometimes we are devils to ourselves,', 'speaker': 'TROILUS', 'type': 'line', 'line_id': 101734}
{'play_name': 'Hamlet', 'speech_number': 16, 'line_number': '1.2.89', 'text_entry': 'Tis sweet and commendable in your nature, Hamlet,', 'speaker': 'KING CLAUDIUS', 'type': 'line', 'line_id': 32724}

{'play_name': 'Measure for measure', 'speech_number': 14, 'line_number': '3.2.43', 'text_entry': 'none of Pygmalions images, newly made woman, to be', 'speaker': 'LUCIO', 'type': 'line', 'line_id': 59929}
{'play_name': 'Antony and Cleopatra', 'speech_number': 49, 'line_number': '5.2.146', 'text_entry': 'Sole sir o the world,', 'speaker': 'CLEOPATRA', 'type': 'line', 'line_id': 22117}

{'play_name': 'Measure for measure', 'speech_number': 165, 'line_number': '5.1.541', 'text_entry': 'One all of luxury, an ass, a madman;', 'speaker': 'DUKE VINCENTIO', 'type': 'line', 'line_id': 61324}
{'play_name': 'Hamlet', 'speech_number': 88, 'line_number': '5.1.225', 'text_entry': 'As we have warrantise: her death was doubtful;', 'speaker': 'First Priest', 'type': 'line', 'line_id': 36136}
